The Chairman, Ogun State House of Assembly Service Commission, Waliu Taiwo has disclosed that every operations at the Commission is being guided by laws, constitutions, legislative practices, procedures and civil service rules. The Chairman made this known during a two day induction and training program for the staffers of the Commission, held in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. According to him, the training was organised to enable the newly employed  and absorbed officers become acquitted with the legislative procedures to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of members of staff. Speaking on the theme, “Understanding the Professional Ethics and Skills for Efficient Service Delivery”, the Chairman encouraged the officers to develop a positive attitude to works in order to achieve high level productivity. On his part, the Clerk of the House, Deji Adeyemo enjoined the officers to contribute their quota to the progress and development of the Commission through effective and qualitative service delivery. He further charged them to give priority to human capacity development and efficient service delivery at work. One of the resource persons and a Director with the Commission, Temitope Okon in his presentation titled, “Overview of the Civil Service with Emphasis on the Ogun State House of Assembly”, said everything in House of Assembly is guided by constitutions and laws, admonishing officers to always follow the rules and regulations of the Commission to guide them on service delivery. Earlier in his welcome address, the Director, of Administration and Supplies of the Commission, Taiwo Opaleye, also noted the need for the officers to always follow and respect the laws and procedures. POLL In their separate reactions, Ayotunde Ojediran, an Administrative officer and Oluwafunmilayo Taiwo, a higher executive officer, commended the leadership of the Commission for the Induction and Training program, saying they have gained a lot, while promising their readiness to deliver.